CS-85
MT Gear Shift Cable
CONTROL SYSTEMS
8. MT Gear Shift Cable
A: REMOVAL
1) Disconnect the ground terminal from battery sensor. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
2) Lift up the vehicle.
3) Remove the center exhaust pipe (rear). <Ref. to EX(w/o STI)-35, REMOVAL, Center Exhaust Pipe.>
4) Remove the center exhaust cover.
5) Remove the cable clamp.

CS-90
MT Gear Shift Cable
CONTROL SYSTEMS
B: INSTALLATION
CAUTION:
Do not bend MT gear shift cable at a sharp angle.
When replacing the new MT gear shift cable, secure it to shift bracket with the clamps, be careful
not to mistake the installing direction.
1) Install the shift bracket together with the MT gear shift cable.
Tightening torque:
18 Nm (1.8 kgf-m, 13.3 ft-lb)
(A) Old MT gear shift cable (B) New MT gear shift cable (C) Shift bracket
(A) MT gear shift cable (B) Shift bracket

4) Insert the MT gear shift cable into cable cover assembly, and install the clamp.
5) Connect the MT gear shift cable.
6) Attach the cable cover plate.

7) Insert the MT gear shift cable into cable clamp, and install to the transmission.

18 Nm (1.8 kgf-m, 13.3 ft-lb)

CS-93
MT Gear Shift Cable
CONTROL SYSTEMS
8) Install the center exhaust cover.
Tightening torque:
18 Nm (1.8 kgf-m, 13.3 ft-lb)
9) Install the center exhaust pipe (rear). <Ref. to EX(w/o STI)-41, INSTALLATION, Center Exhaust Pipe.>
10) Lower the vehicle.
11) Connect the ground terminal to battery sensor. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
12) Make sure the gears can be shifted accurately into each gear.
